The paper discusses the use of supervised learning techniques for brain mapping, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The techniques involve analyzing functional Magnetic Resonance Images (fMRI) data, which is a type of image analysis (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of non-linearities, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of regularization and statistical modeling, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL).
